1
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:07,360
Slow down.

2
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:19,940
The rumors are actually true.

3
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:21,480
Rumor has it

4
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:23,680
that in the Tu Residence,

5
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:25,340
animals often die bizarrely.

6
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:26,200
Some say

7
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:28,330
their vital energy was sucked out.

8
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:55,720
You finally came.

9
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:58,400
How did you know

10
00:01:58,560 --> 00:01:59,560
I would come?

11
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:01,520
I've been waiting for you.

12
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:05,080
Come with me.

13
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:08,380
I have something very important to tell you.

14
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:26,280
Do I owe you money too?

15
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,360
The Tu Residence is so rich.

16
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:30,400
Are they trying to kill me?

17
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:37,920
I've waited for this day for so long.

18
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,460
I didn't expect you to actually come.

19
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:41,680
Thank heavens.

20
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:44,320
I will definitely enjoy it

21
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:45,760
and make the most of it.

22
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:48,120
Are you a cult member?

23
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:50,680
I...

24
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:52,160
I'm not an easy man.

25
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:54,640
Wait!

26
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:56,840
Help!

27
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,360
Liu Chuan, enlighten me!

28
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:02,960
Boss, save me!

29
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:05,040
Liu Chuan,

30
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,920
save me!

31
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:11,640
Get up.

32
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:15,800
Don't hit me!

33
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:25,600
Is there no justice?

34
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:27,520
She assaulted me!

35
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:29,040
She assaulted you?

36
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:32,800
How is that possible?

37
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,180
I just wanted Liu Chuan

38
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,720
to teach me psychic arts.

39
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,920
Psychic arts?

40
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:44,840
The book says

41
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,600
as long as you practice spiritually with a psychic,

42
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:48,640
which means...

43
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,840
Didn't you say

44
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,860
Liu Chuan can make corpses speak?

45
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,160
That's why I...

46
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,480
Which bastard wrote this book?

47
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,840
What was Qin Shi Huang doing?

48
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:00,840
Why didn't he burn this kind of book?

49
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:03,440
It's all because you talk nonsense

50
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:05,120
and cause misunderstandings.

51
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,040
My fault?

52
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,240
My fault.

53
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:12,340
He doesn't know any psychic arts.

54
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:14,360
He only knows how to examine corpses and investigate.

55
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:16,890
Yes, I only examine corpses and investigate.

56
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:19,279
If there are no psychic arts,

57
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:21,360
how do you explain Lailan's matter?

58
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:22,840
It seems

59
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:24,720
this is my fate.

60
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:27,840
Is there something wrong with your friend's head?

61
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:28,400
Shut up.

62
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:30,890
Speaking of Lailan,

63
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:31,720
we stayed in the Tu Residence

64
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,450
secretly just for this matter.

65
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,840
Don't tell anyone.

66
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:38,800
Third Miss,

67
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:40,720
Old Madam Tu has arrived.

68
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:43,170
The whole residence must welcome her.

69
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:44,760
Got it.

70
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:45,880
I'll go now.

71
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:49,970
You hide here first.

72
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:51,440
Don't go out.

73
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,520
Her father died.

74
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:57,080
Why is she so calm?

75
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,740
Yunmeng's mother died early.

76
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,000
Just because she is a woman,

77
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,600
she was left out in the cold in the Tu Residence.

78
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:05,640
If it weren't for the two ladies,

79
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:07,640
she would have been kicked out long ago.

80
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:09,240
Spending all day with these things,

81
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:12,100
how could there be any father-daughter affection?

82
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:14,130
Her father is really ruthless.

83
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:16,380
No wonder she acts so weird every day.

84
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,000
Well...

85
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:20,240
What did Old Dowager Tu do again?

86
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:23,440
What are you doing?

87
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:24,640
Are you going to hit me?

88
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:26,360
Did I damage your brain?

89
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:28,850
You don't even know Old Dowager Tu?

90
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:34,840
I just have a bit of temporary amnesia.

91
00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:36,240
Help me remember.

92
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,440
Old Dowager Tu's grandfather

93
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:41,640
was a meritorious general who fought for Emperor Taizu and Taizong.

94
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:43,800
She herself also went to battle.

95
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,240
Her breaking of worldly conventions

96
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,500
commands our respect.

97
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:51,170
No wonder the Tu family is so domineering.

98
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:52,520
I remember now.

99
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,080
Good. That's good.

100
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:55,840
What?

101
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:57,440
Are you worried about me?

102
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,000
I'm just afraid your brain is damaged,

103
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,600
delaying my investigation.

104
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:02,680
Heartless woman.

105
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:06,720
Oh no.

106
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:08,320
What's wrong now?

107
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:12,440
Your best friend likes tinkering with these things.

108
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,920
She acts weird every day.

109
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:16,040
Now there's a rumor of a moving corpse in the Tu Manor.

110
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:18,240
Ignorant people might

111
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:20,100
forcibly connect the two things.

112
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:21,640
That's indeed possible.

113
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:23,300
We must quickly think of a way.

114
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:25,040
We sneaked into the Tu Manor.

115
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:27,000
To prove it has nothing to do with her,

116
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,260
we also need evidence.

117
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,040
I got it.

118
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:44,720
Master Tu's body has already been placed in the mourning hall.

119
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:47,040
Are there any clues on this dried corpse?

120
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:49,900
Since we can't find any useful clues,

121
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:51,680
we might as well start with this dried corpse

122
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:53,210
to prove she isn't a zombie.

123
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:55,440
This is called proof by contradiction.

124
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,120
How do we prove that?

125
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:01,650
What can this dried corpse reveal?

126
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,040
What are you doing?

127
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,800
A human face has 36 main bone points,

128
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:12,740
which are inevitably connected.

129
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,200
After determining the bone points

130
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,400
and connecting them,

131
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:18,000
we can restore most of the original face.

132
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:19,440
If we had a computer,

133
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:21,570
the restoration would be even better.

134
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:23,400
Never mind seventy or eighty percent.

135
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,080
As long as there's a rough outline,

136
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:27,540
the Tu family will definitely recognize it.

137
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,920
What is this computer you mentioned?

138
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,380
Is it really that magical?

139
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:33,040
Then we should get one too.

140
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:37,170
I'm afraid we'd have to wait thousands of years for that.

141
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,200
Why does this person look so familiar?

142
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,600
By order of the Old Dowager,

143
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,480
surround the courtyard.

144
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,840
No one is allowed in or out.

145
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:20,880
Violators will be killed without mercy.
